# NOTE: Keep this list short (~8 entries). Remove old ones as new ones land.
CHANGELOG = [
    "b407: F25-plant probes the F30-F50 wall + caster combat wedge fix. The user's directive was 'stronger F25 plants to find and break the F30-F50 wall'. Baseline (b406, 1500T, 30 seeds, F25 plant): dwarf 3/30 (avg max F26.8), elf 10/30 (F25.2), human 3/30 (F25.4) -- plants died too fast on F25 to even probe the F30 wall, and the smart-policy descent gate (line 6260, weakly_geared_d = (eq_w+eq_a) < (2*z+3)) refused descent at F25 since maxed starter Dagger+Leather can't clear 53. Six coordinated changes turned plant strength up enough to expose the real wall: (1) target_level N-2 -> N+1 (F25 plant L23 -> L26), (2) elixir_bonus N//5 -> N//4 (F25 +5 -> +6 each stat), (3) upg (N-1)//3 -> (N-1)//2 (F25 +8 -> +12 with cap from weapon's upgrade_limit), (4) gear swap by tier: F15+ Adamantine Sword + Dragon Scale, F20+ Volcanic Blade + Volcanic Mail, F25+ Enchanted Longsword + Enchanted Plate -- at F25 the gear bar lands at 76 (vs 53 threshold), descent gate clears, (5) Tier 6 inventory at F25+: Antidote x3 (cure_all), Master Healing Potion x3 extra, Restoration Scroll x2, Teleport Scroll x2, Bratwurst x6 (sausages don't rot, outlasts the 7000T food clock), (6) base_max_health_bonus += (N-1)*5 and base_max_mana_bonus += (N-1)*3 (F25 elf 290 -> 410 HP, 270 -> 342 MP) -- the b407 death audit showed status-lockout (Frost Worm freeze, Basilisk paralysis, Gorgon petrify) killed casters in 2-3 swings of 50-80 dmg without an HP buffer to absorb. Bonus bug fixes: (a) wedge-break in combat_mode was returning 'x' (combat.py:1271 rejects 'x' as 'Invalid combat command'); F25 elf seed=4 burned 2919 turns firing invalid 'x' against a Werewolf because Mage Armor / Stone Skin buffs don't change HP / kills / position so freeze_streak hit 30. Now returns 'f' for combat_mode wedge-trips. (b) freeze_key now includes mana so a caster buffing themselves in combat counts as world progress and doesn't trip the wedge. Final 3000T sweep (30 seeds, F25 plant): dwarf 21/30 (70%, avg max F34.7, max F41), elf 11/30 (37%, F30.5, F39), human 12/30 (40%, F29.1, F37). The F30-F50 wall is visible: dwarves hit it around F40-F41, casters around F35-F39, F25-F30 transition still claims many casters via status-lockout monsters and big-hit elites (Death Knight 90 dmg, Demilich 98 dmg, Storm Giant 72 dmg + Burn).",
    "b405: Spectral Hand + Mage Armor toned down. The b404 sweep correctly broke the F25 caster wall but went too far: F25 elf 24/30 (80%) and F25 human 21/30 (70%) survived vs F25 dwarf 8/30 (27%), inverting the intended caster=glass-cannon / dwarf=tank archetype. Two targeted nerfs: (1) Spectral Hand 3-absorb / 8-turn / 14 MP -> 1-absorb / 4-turn / 16 MP. Was effectively erasing ~240 raw F25 damage per cast (3 hits * ~80 dmg/swing); now it's a single-absorb insurance card for one critical hit, with shorter window and higher mana cost. (2) Mage Armor +6 DEF / 10 turns -> +4 DEF / 6 turns. Combined with Stone Skin's +8 DEF for 4 turns, casters were stacking +14 DEF which made F25 hits effectively single-digit. Now +12 DEF stacked (still strong, but enemies land 3-4x more damage). Both spells remain mana-efficient defensive options -- Mage Armor still 3 DEF-turns per MP, beating Stone Skin's 1.78. Target after b405: casters land in the 25-45% F25 survival band, dwarf martial baseline (27%) competitive. Pre-combat buff casting (the b404 wishlist item) intentionally NOT added -- F25 numbers were already too high.",
    "b404: fix spell priority + monster obs in spell_casting_mode + Talisman as random drop. b403 audit (18 caster seeds across F15/F25) revealed three bugs that left the new caster suite essentially inactive: (1) Hold Monster cast 0 times across all 18 audit runs because Stone Skin was first in the spell_casting_mode cascade and always fired when defense_boost wasn't active -- Hold Monster never reached. (2) Mage Armor and Spectral Hand never cast either, for the same priority-order reason. (3) F25 elf hit the 24-slot memorize cap before Spectral Hand could be added (Mage Armor + Spectral Hand were at the tail of the tier list, dropped when the slot budget ran out). (4) _monster_obs returned None outside combat_mode, so the spell_casting_mode tough_fight gate (m_max_hp >= 30% pc max) always evaluated False even when the policy correctly transitioned modes. Six coordinated fixes: rewrote spell_casting_mode priority to Hold Monster -> Spectral Hand -> Mage Armor -> Stone Skin -> Heal -> Damage (Stone Skin no longer fires first); each defensive layer now gates on its own status_effect_name rather than the shared 'defense_boost' effect_type, so Mage Armor + Stone Skin can stack for +14 DEF; reordered _grant_memorized_spells tier list to put Mage Armor / Spectral Hand BEFORE Battle Hymn + Purify so the F25 24-slot budget actually fits them; surfaced gs.active_monster in spell_casting_mode obs; removed the b403 Hourglass Talisman auto-grant from plant baseline and added it to UNIQUE_TREASURE_TEMPLATES (level 4) so it spawns via the same 10%-chest / vault-reward path as Heartstone Pendant + Wizard's Monocle. Audit verification (18 seeds): F25 elf went from 0/18 surviving (b403) to 14/18 (78%); F25 human 0 -> 11/18 (61%). Hold Monster cast 47-49% of all casts; Mage Armor and Spectral Hand each active ~35 turns per run.",
    "Caster defense suite: Hold Monster opener + DEX concentration + Mage Armor + Spectral Hand + Hourglass Talisman (build 403). Six coordinated changes addressing the F25 cast-attrition wall from b402 death diag (15/30 elf deaths and 13/30 human deaths happened in spell_casting_mode). (1) Fixed Hold Monster: pre-b403 the L0 cantrip applied time_stop to the target but the post-instant-cast monster swing at combat.py:1880 had no time_stop check, so the freeze did nothing on the cast-turn counter-attack. Added the check; also bumped status duration 1->2 so the freeze survives the start-of-next-turn process_status_effects tick AND covers the L2 follow-up's channel-init swing. Hold Monster + L2 spell sequence now takes 1 monster swing instead of 2. (2) Smart-policy Hold Monster opener: spell_casting_mode picks Hold Monster first when target isn't already held/paralyzed AND an affordable damage spell is queued AND the fight is worth the 1-MP/1-turn investment (m_max_hp >= pc_max_hp * 0.30 prey filter). Classic D&D wizard 'buy a round of concentration' trick. (3) Humans now start with Hold Monster cantrip alongside Mind Touch (still gated by INT > 13 cast threshold). (4) DEX added to concentration_check modifier (+ self.dexterity // 4 alongside existing INT // 4) so the duelist-mage build pushed by b399 + b402 actually wins concentration saves under fire. F25 elf modifier 6 -> 11, success rate on a 40-dmg DC 20 check climbs 30% -> 55%. (5) Two new spells: Mage Armor (L1, 8 MP, +6 DEF for 10 turns -- cheap persistent buff for mid-game humans) and Spectral Hand (L2, 14 MP, absorbs next 3 enemy strikes for 8 turns -- new 'hit_absorb' status effect type that consumes whole hits in characters.py:take_damage before damage reduction applies). Both pre-memorized to F10+ / F15+ caster plants via _grant_memorized_spells. (6) New accessory: Hourglass Talisman (treasure_type='passive', +20% cast_speed_bonus, +2 INT, granted + auto-equipped to F18+ caster plants). cast_speed_bonus stacks with the b402 INT-scaled quick-cast roll; cap raised 50 -> 75 so a Talisman + INT 25 elf hits 52% chance to skip channel-init swing. (7) Sprite assignments: Mage Armor -> I047 (Divine Shield visual), Spectral Hand -> I058 (Stone Skin defensive aura), Hourglass Talisman -> Heartstone Pendant sprites (pendant visuals).",
    "Quick Cast: INT-scaled skip-the-channel-init-swing for casters (build 402). Death diagnostic on b401 F25 caster failures revealed the F25 wall isn't 1-shot kills (0/30 across elf+human) -- it's cast-turn attrition: 15/30 elf deaths and 13/30 human deaths happened in spell_casting_mode. Each L2-L3 spell channels 1 turn before firing, and the monster swings during the channel-init turn (~80-90 raw at F25) AND again after the spell fires. A 3-spell sequence (Stone Skin -> Mass Heal -> Flame Lance) burns 240-270 raw dmg taken across 6 monster swings against monsters the caster can't kill in time. New caster identity feature: high-INT casters roll (INT - 17) * 4% chance per L2+ cast to skip the channel-init monster swing -- 'arcane reflexes finish the spell instantly'. Capped at 50%. Curve: INT 18 -> 4%, INT 20 -> 12%, INT 22 -> 20%, INT 25 -> 32%, INT 28 -> 44%, INT 30+ -> 50%. The channel-complete swing (after spell fires) is intentionally left intact so the monster still gets a counter-action -- quick-cast only buys back the channeling 'lock-in' period, not the whole exchange. Tracks via gs.game_stats.quick_casts. Smoke test on seed 42 F25 elf: 3 quick-casts out of 4 spells cast (high variance on small sample, expected 32%). Saves ~80 raw dmg per quick-cast trigger.",
    "Short-fight-prey filter on Stone Skin buff (build 401). The b400 audit showed F25 elf spending 78% of cast budget on defense (Stone Skin 26) vs offense (Flame Lance 8). The m_level >= pc_level - 1 gate fired on every parity-level fight, including against small-HP enemies that would die in 1-2 alpha-strikes regardless of Stone Skin -- the 18 MP + 1-turn buff cost never paid back on those. Added a second gate: m_max_hp >= pc_max_hp * 0.30, filtering out short-fight prey while still triggering on the long-fight bosses where Stone Skin's 4-turn +8 DEF window pays back. Brief detour through an hp_pct < 0.75 gate (defer buff until already-hurt) regressed F15 elf 6/30 -> 1/30 because the elf took the big hit BEFORE the buff fired -- preemptive on turn 1 was correct; the over-firing fix is the prey filter, not deferral. F15 elf Stone Skin trigger now skips fights against weak ~50-HP monsters that the elf one-shots with Lightning Bolt at INT 19 (58 dmg after b400 scaling), preserving the buff investment for fights that last 3+ turns.",
    "Additive INT-scaling layer on spell damage / healing (build 400). The b399 caster sweep showed mana regen alone didn't move F20-F25 caster survival -- elf 0/30 at F25 even with full-cast budget. Audit traced it to spell damage staying flat across stat investment on low-tier spells: Mind Touch (L0) at INT 25 only hit for 18 vs 12 at INT 12 because the existing int_bonus formula's per-level multiplier (`max(0, INT-10) * spell.level // 3`) gave nothing to L0 cantrips. A cantrip-only caster (e.g. F15 human Mind Touch) got zero scaling reward for the b397 elixir-pad INT investment. Added a flat `max(0, (INT-15)//2)` bonus on top of the existing per-level scaling, applied in both spell-cast paths -- combat.py:_execute_charged_spell and characters.py:Character.cast_spell. Damage at INT 25: Mind Touch 18 -> 23 (+28%), Lightning Bolt 53 -> 58 (+9%), Flame Lance 55 -> 60 (+9%). Healing at INT 25: Mass Heal 72 -> 77 HP. The scaling is intentionally modest on high-level spells (already over-scaled by int_bonus) but meaningful on L0-L1 spells where the prior formula's level multiplier was 0-1. Side benefit: F15 human cantrip-only casters now see Mind Touch climb 6 -> 13 dmg (INT 16, no int_bonus contribution from L0 spells), making cantrips a real combat option instead of strictly worse than melee swings at L13.",
    "Race + INT-scaled mana regen for caster identity (build 399). The b398 spell pick + Stone Skin fixes lifted F15 caster survival 3-4x (elf 5% -> 23%, human 8% -> 30%), but F20-F25 casters still cratered (elf 7% / 0%, human 7% / 0%). The b398 audit showed casters were getting 65 MP/fight worth of value out of their spellbook -- Stone Skin 18 + Flame Lance 17 + Mass Heal 30 -- but the uniform 1 MP / 5 moves regen rate replenished only 3 MP across a typical 15-move room transit, so the second fight could only afford one spell instead of three. Rewrote process_mana_regen in items.py with race-flavored tick intervals and an INT-scaled per-tick gain. New curve: elf 1 tick / 2 moves, human 1 tick / 3 moves, dwarf 1 tick / 5 moves (unchanged -- magic is hard for them); per-tick MP = 1 + (INT - 16) // 4 so a high-INT caster scales gain alongside cost. Effective rates: F15 elf (INT ~19) 50 MP/100 moves, F25 elf (INT ~25) 150 MP/100 moves (vs 20 MP/100 moves pre-b399 for everyone). The F25 elf's 237 max_mana now fully regenerates across ~160 moves of exploration -- sustainable across a long session instead of decaying to zero by mid-run. Dwarf regen unchanged because they're not the caster race; their identity is HP-tank, not mana-throughput. F20 elf cast rate jumped 63% -> 77% in the audit and F25 elf 57% -> 65% -- they're now casting through fights instead of stretching mana between them. Combined with the b397 stat-elixir pad + b398 power-aware spell pick, this should close the elf/human survival gap at F20+ vs the dwarf martial baseline.",
]
